radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung bases are clear. Liver is homogeneous with no focal lesions. No biliary ductal dilatation. Gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys are normal. Distal portion of the appendix is dilated up to 12 mm, demonstrates an appendicolith, and is fluid filled, surrounded by fat stranding. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. Intra-abdominal aorta is normal. Small amount of free fluid in the pelvis. No focal lytic or sclerotic osseous lesion suspicious for infection or malignancy.
